=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LotkaVolterra_ex3 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with square_like oscillator character around 50 Hz, featuring punchy attack and compressed envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: compressed
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -8.9404
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9456
  pitch_clarity: 0.0515
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: square_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -10.3931
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LotkaVolterra Example 3
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LotkaVolterra.html
// Tags: LotkaVolterra, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 3 ---
// scope signals, set graphics to 'xy' to see relations between predator (out 0) and prey (out 1)
{LotkaVolterra.ar(SampleRate.ir*0.5, \a.kr(1.5, 0.1), \b.kr(1.5, 0.1), \c.kr(0.5, 0.1), \d.kr(1.5, 0.1), h: \h.kr(0.01), xi: 0.1 + \tr.tr(1))}.play;
